Resource	Aura File		Lightning Web Components File	
	File Extension	syntax	File Extension	syntax
Markup	sample.cmp	"<aura:component>
</aura:component>"	sample.html	"<template>
</template>"
Declearing attributes	sample.cmp	"<aura:component>
<aura:attribute name=""var1"" type=""String""/>
</aura:component>"	sample.js [Please note that we can't declare attributes in  html file.So, we have to swith that part to JS file. Attributes in aura compoent file = properties in LWC Js file]	"import { LightningElement, api } from 'lwc';
export default class PropertySummary extends LightningElement 
{
    @api var1;
    property;
}
Here : 
@api - Is a Decorator. 
Usage: To mark variable as public. So that this variable value can be set 
a]. from Appbuilder or
b]. by a parent component that uses the component in its markup."
